===Etymology===
[[bearded]] + [[mussel]]; both this and the specific epithet ''[[barbatus]]'' refer to the long bristles which protrude from the [[periostracum]], appearing to coat the shell in hair.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a coastal mussel of Britain, ''[[Modiolus barbatus]]''.

